<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A woman luckily avoided serious injury after she fell from a moving car on the M25 as she leaned from a window to grab a video for Snapchat.</p>

<p>The un-named woman fell from the vehicle between junction six and the Clacket Lane Services at 1.30am today into a 'live lane.'</p>

<p>Surrey Police officers Tweeted about the accident. The woman was not badly hurt but the police added that it was lucky 'she wasn't seriously injured or killed.'</p>

<p>The un-named woman fell from the car between junction six and the Clacket Lane Services</p>

<p>No arrests have been made in regards to the incident and the woman was treated by paramedics at the scene.Â </p>

<p>The Surrey force's Roads Policing Unit Tweeted: 'The front seat passenger was hanging out the car whilst filming a Snapchat video along the M25. She then fell out the car and into a live lane.</p>

<p>'It is only by luck she wasn't seriously injured or killed. #nowords'</p>

<p>Surrey Police's Roads Policing Unit Tweeted about the accident</p>

<p>A police spokesman said: 'Officers were called to the M25 between junction six and Clacket Lane Services shortly after 01.30 this morning following reports of a female falling out of a moving vehicle.</p>

<p>'The woman was treated by paramedics at the scene and her injuries were not life-threatening or life-changing.'</p>
